OL,3,CReforms of new Troubles commission
OL,4,Cneeded to secure trust of families,
OL,5,Csays Benn
OL,7,FHowever, last year the Court of Appeal
OL,8,Fin Belfast ruled that a Government
OL,9,Fveto power over what sensitive
OL,10,Fmaterial can be disclosed to families
OL,11,Fby the commission is incompatible with
OL,12,Fhuman rights laws.
OL,14,FThe court also found that the work of
OL,15,Fthe commission does not provide
OL,16,Fvictims and their next of kin adequate
OL,17,Fmeans to participate in its processes.
OL,19,FThe Appeal Court judges did uphold the
OL,20,Foperational independence of the
OL,21,Fcommission's structures.
